# Frontend QA Testing Guide — Cordinal Mushrooms

> **Before you start**: Open the app at [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.
> All tests below are manual browser tests — the app stores data in the browser's IndexedDB.

---

## ✅ 1. Dashboard

| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 1.1 | Navigate to `/` | Dashboard loads with two sections: "Fruiting / Incubation Room" and "Storage Room" |
| 1.2 | Check each card shows a **Total** count | Total reflects real batch/inventory counts |
| 1.3 | Create a batch 22+ days ago (use production page). Come back to dashboard | "To Harvest" badge appears in green |
| 1.4 | Create a batch for Day 1 of a LC type | "To shake" count should appear in red if not shaken |
| 1.5 | Add a Base Culture inventory item that is 160+ days old | "About to expire" appears in amber in Storage Room |
| 1.6 | Resize browser to mobile (375px) | Cards stack single-column; all numbers visible without overflow |

---

## ✅ 2. Facility — Rack View

### 2a. Rack Management
| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 2.1 | Navigate to `/facility` | All racks shown on the floor plan canvas |
| 2.2 | Click **Add Rack** | Form opens; fill Name, Capacity, Layers → rack appears on canvas |
| 2.3 | Drag a rack to a new position | Position persists on reload |
| 2.4 | Toggle **Lights** switch on a rack | `lightStatus` updates; dashboard "In light/darkness" counts shift |
| 2.5 | Click **Duplicate** | New rack appears with [(Copy)](file:///d:/myworks/Mushroom_Operations/hooks/use-production.ts#68-69) suffix, empty batches |
| 2.6 | Delete a rack **with** active batches | Error: "Cannot delete rack with active batches" |
| 2.7 | Delete a rack **without** active batches | Rack removed from canvas |

### 2b. Layer Actions (inside Rack Detail dialog)
| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 2.8 | Click a rack → Rack Detail dialog opens | Shows all layers; occupied layers display batch name, type, jar count |
| 2.9 | Coloured glow on a layer cell | 🔵 Blue = Put/Remove Cloth due, 🟡 Yellow = Switch Lights, 🟢 Green = Harvest ready, 🔴 Red = Discard, 🟣 Purple = Shake needed |

### 2c. Batch Actions (per batch row in Rack Detail)
| # | Action | Step | Expected Result |
|---|--------|------|----------------|
| 2.10 | **Shake** (LC batch, Day 0–5) | Click Shake button | Logs "Shake" action; shake count for the day increments; purple glow clears if 2/2 done |
| 2.11 | **Mist** | Click Mist button on any batch | Logs "Mist" action; visible in History dialog |
| 2.12 | **Put Cloth** | Click Put Cloth on a fresh batch | Logs "Put Cloth"; blue glow should appear when cloth-removal day approaches |
| 2.13 | **Remove Cloth** | Click Remove Cloth on a batch that has cloth | Logs "Remove Cloth"; blue glow disappears from that layer |
| 2.14 | **Harvest** (from rack view) | Click Harvest on a ready batch | Batch status → Harvested; inventory item created; layer clears; rack usage decreases |
| 2.15 | **Discard Partial** | Enter quantity < jarCount in Discard dialog | Only that quantity is discarded; remaining jars stay in batch; a Waste item is added to inventory |
| 2.16 | **Discard Full** | Discard all jars | Batch status → Discarded; layer clears; batch appears in Waste Management graveyard |
| 2.17 | **Move Items** | Select source layer+qty → pick target rack+layer | `batchLocations` updated; source rack usage decreases; target rack usage increases |

