## ✅ 3. Production — Active Production

| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 3.1 | Navigate to `/production` → "Active Production" tab | Table shows all non-Harvested/Discarded batches |
| 3.2 | Click **New Batch** | Dialog opens with fields: Name, Type, Source, Start Date, Rack, Layer, Jar Count |
| 3.3 | Fill in and submit a new batch | Batch appears in table; rack usage updates in Facility |
| 3.4 | Click **Harvest** on a batch | Batch disappears from Active; reappears in Stored Items tab with source/location data |
| 3.5 | Click **Discard** on a batch | Batch moves to Waste tab graveyard |
| 3.6 | Click ✏️ edit on a batch | Edit dialog opens; change name/jar count and save → table updates |
| 3.7 | Click **History** button | Dialog shows past actions (Shake/Mist) and Past Locations tab |
| 3.8 | Click **Log Action** (Shake, Mist, etc.) | Action saved; appears in History dialog |

---

## ✅ 4. Production — Stored Items

| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 4.1 | Switch to "Stored Items" tab | Table shows: Batch ID, Name, Type, Qty, Unit, Source, Past Location, Batch Start Date, Date Added, History |
| 4.2 | Verify Batch ID shows `#<number>` for harvested items | Correct ID from originating batch |
| 4.3 | Verify Source column | Shows `sourceId` from the batch (e.g. "Master-LC-001") |
| 4.4 | Verify Past Location | Shows rack name + layer (e.g. "Rack A / L3") |
| 4.5 | Click **History** on a stored item | BatchHistoryDialog opens with Actions + Past Locations tabs |
| 4.6 | Manually-added inventory items | Source, Batch ID, Past Location all show `—` |

---

## ✅ 5. Production — Waste Management

| # | Action | Expected Result |
|---|--------|----------------|
| 5.1 | Switch to "Waste" tab | Two sections: "Discarded Batches (Graveyard)" and "Inventory Waste" |
| 5.2 | Discarded Batches table columns | Batch ID, Source, Type, Batch Start Date, Discarded Date, Jars, Status |
| 5.3 | Verify Discarded Date | Shows the date the batch was discarded (not creation date) |
| 5.4 | Inventory Waste table columns | Item Name, Source, Type, Batch Start Date, Discarded Date, Quantity, Status |
| 5.5 | Click **History** on a waste item with a linked batch | Dialog opens with correct action history |

